  "answer": "Table 5.2 restates the pmf with an additional row listing values for $x \cdot \operatorname{Pr}(X=x)$. The expected value, calculated below the table, is $\mu=3.00$. We expect three successes over the long run.

\begin{table}
\captionsetup{labelformat=empty}
\caption{Table 5.2 Calculation of expected value for the "Four patients" illustration example.}
\begin{tabular}{lccccc}
\hline$x$ & 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 \\
$\operatorname{Pr}(X=x)$ & 0.0039 & 0.0469 & 0.2109 & 0.4219 & 0.3164 \\
$x \cdot \operatorname{Pr}(X=x)$ & $0.0000^a$ & $0.0469^b$ & $0.4218^c$ & 1.2657 & 1.2656 \\
\hline
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

Examples of calculations:

$$
\begin{aligned}
& { }^a x \cdot \operatorname{Pr}(X=0)=0 \cdot 0.0039=0.0000 \\
& { }^b x \cdot \operatorname{Pr}(X=1)=1 \cdot 0.0469=0.0469 \\
& { }^c x \cdot \operatorname{Pr}(X=2)=2 \cdot 0.2109=0.4218
\end{aligned}
$$


Calculation of the expected value:

$$
\mu=\Sigma x \cdot \operatorname{Pr}(X=x)=0.0000+0.0469+0.4218+1.2657+1.2656=3.00
$$


Table 5.3 restates the pmf with an additional row listing values for $(x-\mu)^2 \cdot \operatorname{Pr}(X=x)$. The variance of the model is calculated below the table revealing $\sigma^2=0.75$. This is a measure of the random variable's variability.
\begin{table}
\captionsetup{labelformat=empty}
\caption{Table 5.3 Calculation of variance for the Four patients illustrative example.}
\begin{tabular}{lccccc}
\hline$x$ & 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 \\
$\operatorname{Pr}(X=x)$ & 0.0039 & 0.0469 & 0.2109 & 0.4219 & 0.3164 \\
$(x-\mu)^2 \cdot \operatorname{Pr}(X=x)$ & $0.0351^a$ & $0.1876^b$ & $0.2109^c$ & 0.0000 & 0.3164 \\
\hline
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

Recall that $\mu=3$.
**Examples of calculations:

$$
\begin{aligned}
& { }^a(x-\mu)^2 \cdot \operatorname{Pr}(X=x)=(0 \cdot 3)^2 \cdot 0.0039=0.0351 \\
& { }^b(x-\mu)^2 \cdot \operatorname{Pr}(X=x)=(1 \cdot 3)^2 \cdot 0.0469=0.1876 \\
& { }^c(x-\mu)^2 \cdot \operatorname{Pr}(X=x)=(2 \cdot 3)^2 \cdot 0.2109=0.2109
\end{aligned}
$$


Calculation of variance:

$$
\sigma^2=\Sigma(x-\mu)^2 \cdot \operatorname{Pr}(X=x)=0.0351+0.1876+0.2109+0.0000+0.3164=0.75
$$",
